<HEADLINE> Kenyan Schools To Adopt Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 30 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
today ordered schools from primary to university level to
furnish environmental conservation education among other subjects.
</P>
<P>
He said this education should emphasize that the
survival of human, animal and plant life depends on the
environment.
</P>
<P>
President Moi was speaking to Maseno University College
students on his way to Kisumu from Vihiga, western Kenya,the Kenya
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
He said it is alarming that Lake Victoria and other water
masses in the country are about to dry up because of the
current wanton destruction of the catchment area.
</P>
<P>
Noting the situation, the president said he will vigorously
enforce conservation measures through the relevant agencies.
</P>
<P>
He called on all communities in Kenya to embrace
environmental conservation as part of their cultures. 
</P>
